      "content": "hey so i was reading about some court cases where religious groups are fighting government laws (like health mandates or stuff) because of their faith. in your opinion, should religious orgs be allowed to opt-out of these mandates if it conflicts with their beliefs, or does that just undermine the secular nature of the state? which side is more important here?",
